Even as such, using full words is barely any more typing, and more readable.<p><pre><code>  [1, 2, 3].each { |value| puts value }
  Object.methods.each { |method| "Method is: #{method}" }
</code></pre>
I consider that a better habit to have than using single-character variables.  And style guides should be about encouraging the best habits possible.
